oc:kn_05a22315 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing the post-cancel confirmation page" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Your subscription has been cancelled.

What happens next:
• Your access continues until [billing period end date]
• Your data will be preserved for [90] days
• You can reactivate anytime from your account settings

[Reactivate My Account]""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "billing period end date",
        "data retention days" .

oc:kn_0981bc57 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing B2C/self-serve cancel flows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Significant cancellations happen on mobile. Cancel flows must be mobile-optimized with clear CTAs." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Mobile cancellations are a measurable chunk of churn; clunky mobile UX increases accidental cancellation frustration" .

oc:kn_24f626b6 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing B2B/team plan cancel flows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Route accounts by MRR: <$100 fully automated, $100-$500 automated with CS flag, $500-$2,000 route to CS before cancel completes, $2,000+ block self-serve and require CS call." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Higher MRR accounts justify personal outreach and have higher save rates (30-45%) when handled by customer success" .

oc:kn_2ec58c39 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When segmenting cancel flow for recently signed-up customers" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For new customers (<30 days), the save is onboarding, not discounts. Offer a free onboarding call, setup help, or extended trial instead." ;
    oc:hasRationale "New cancellers haven't activated yet — discounts won't fix a value-realization problem" .

oc:kn_65fee68c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When cancel reason is 'switching to competitor'" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Ask which competitor (optional) 2. Show comparison if available 3. Offer migration credit (match their price for 3 months) 4. Request 15-min feedback call" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_794ef9dd a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing pause subscription reactivation emails" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Pause reactivation sequence:
- Day -7: "Your pause ends in 7 days. We've been busy — here's what's new."
- Day -1: "Welcome back tomorrow! Here's what's waiting for you."
- Day 0: "You're back! Here's a quick tour of what's new.\"""" .

oc:kn_bd3411c3 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing the discount ladder in cancel flows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never lead with your biggest discount. Escalate offers gradually (15% → 25% → let go). Maximum 2 discount offers per cancel session, never exceed 30%." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Leading with the biggest discount trains users to cancel-for-discount behavior and devalues the product" ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_beac7c78 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When implementing a cancel flow from scratch" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Phase 1 (Week 1): Add cancel flow with survey + 1 offer + confirmation, map one offer per cancel reason, track metrics 2. Phase 2 (Weeks 2-4): Add fallback offers, implement pause, set up dunning sequence, enable smart retries, add MRR routing 3. Phase 3 (Month 2+): Build health score, proactive triggers, A/B test offers, segment flows, win-back sequence, cohort analysis" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_c62a9288 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "All cancel flows, especially those targeting US consumers under FTC rules" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Cancellation must be as easy as signup. Cannot require a phone call to cancel if signup was online. 'Continue cancelling' must be clear at every step." ;
    oc:hasRationale "FTC Click-to-Cancel rule mandates easy cancellation; dark patterns create legal liability and brand damage" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_c8af16c2 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When choosing between discount vs pause as a save offer" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Pause is often better than a discount because it doesn't devalue your product. Limit pauses to 1 per 12-month period, max 3 months, with auto-reactivation and 7-day advance email." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Pauses preserve perceived product value while giving users a break; longer pauses rarely result in reactivation" .

oc:kn_d009948c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting up the post-cancel email sequence" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Post-cancel sequence: Immediately → confirmation email. Day 7 → NPS/satisfaction survey. Day 30 → 'what's new' email. Day 60 → address their specific cancel reason if resolved. Day 90 → final win-back with special offer. Day 1 → do nothing (don't be desperate)." ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

oc:kn_f9bf0444 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SecurityImplication ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When handling post-cancel data for EU users under GDPR" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Inform users about data retention period post-cancel, offer data export before account deletion, honor deletion requests within 30 days, and don't use post-cancel data for marketing without consent." ;
    oc:hasRationale "GDPR non-compliance can result in significant fines and reputational damage" ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

